<n-docbody><doc bill="Y"><content.metadata.block><cmd.identifiers><cmd.cites><cmd.second.line.cite><bop/><bos/>Ga. Evidence § 4:3<eos/><eop/></cmd.second.line.cite></cmd.cites></cmd.identifiers></content.metadata.block><prop.block><prop.head toc-guid=""><bop/><bos/><headtext>Agnor&apos;s Georgia Evidence</headtext><eos/><eop/></prop.head><content.metadata.block><cmd.dates><cmd.currency.default iso.d="20191101"><bop/><bos/>November 2019 Update<eos/><eop/></cmd.currency.default></cmd.dates></content.metadata.block><author.line><bop/><bos/><author>Ana Marcela Rountree</author><eos/><eop/></author.line><prop.head toc-guid="I266c3570630a11eab5989292d3e01631"><bop/><bos/><label.name>Chapter</label.name><label.designator>4.</label.designator><headtext>Constitutional Privileges</headtext><eos/><eop/></prop.head></prop.block><message.block><include.copyright n-include_collection="w_wlnv_msg" n-include_guid="I1DA35ED81DD211B281BAD200220BDFCA">Copr. (C) West 2005 No Claim to Orig. U.S. Govt. Works</include.copyright></message.block><section><section.front><doc.title toc-guid="Id71f53c9682311ea83aee46e6decbb85"><head parent="doc.title"><bop/><bos/><label.name>§ </label.name><label.designator>4:3.</label.designator><headtext>Privilege against self-incrimination</headtext><eos/><eop/></head></doc.title></section.front><section.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>There are two main divisions of the privilege against self-incrimination: one protects a person charged with a criminal offense and the other protects witnesses whose testimony may incriminate them. <eos/><bos/>These divisions can be subdivided into four applications:</paratext><list><list.item><para><head parent="para"><label.designator>(1)</label.designator></head><paratext>The privilege of an accused in a criminal case not to be a witness against himself.[<eos/><bos/><footnote.reference refid="I7766359074d311ea92c4fb7908f1a7b5">1</footnote.reference>]</paratext></para></list.item><list.item><para><head parent="para"><label.designator>(2)</label.designator></head><paratext>The privilege of an accused to remain silent.[<eos/><bos/><footnote.reference refid="I77665ca074d311ea92c4fb7908f1a7b5">2</footnote.reference>]</paratext></para></list.item><list.item><para><head parent="para"><label.designator>(3)</label.designator></head><paratext>The privilege of an accused to not incriminate himself through non-testimonial actions.[<eos/><bos/><footnote.reference refid="I77665ca274d311ea92c4fb7908f1a7b5">3</footnote.reference>]</paratext></para></list.item><list.item><para><head parent="para"><label.designator>(4)</label.designator></head><paratext>The privilege of any witness not to testify to incriminating facts.[<eos/><bos/><footnote.reference refid="I776683b174d311ea92c4fb7908f1a7b5">4</footnote.reference>]</paratext></para></list.item></list><eos/><eop/></para></section.body></section><footnote.block><footnote ID="I7766359074d311ea92c4fb7908f1a7b5"><label.designator>1</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>See <cite.query w-ref-type="DA" w-normalized-cite="GAEVIDENCES4:4" w-pub-number="160247" ID="I7766359174d311ea92c4fb7908f1a7b5">§ 4:4</cite.query>, infra.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote><footnote ID="I77665ca074d311ea92c4fb7908f1a7b5"><label.designator>2</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>See <cite.query w-ref-type="DA" w-normalized-cite="GAEVIDENCES4:6" w-pub-number="160247" ID="I77665ca174d311ea92c4fb7908f1a7b5">§ 4:6</cite.query>, infra.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote><footnote ID="I77665ca274d311ea92c4fb7908f1a7b5"><label.designator>3</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>See <cite.query w-ref-type="DA" w-normalized-cite="GAEVIDENCES4:7" w-pub-number="160247" ID="I776683b074d311ea92c4fb7908f1a7b5">§ 4:7</cite.query>, infra.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote><footnote ID="I776683b174d311ea92c4fb7908f1a7b5"><label.designator>4</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>See <cite.query w-ref-type="DA" w-normalized-cite="GAEVIDENCES4:8" w-pub-number="160247" ID="I776683b274d311ea92c4fb7908f1a7b5">§ 4:8</cite.query>, infra.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote></footnote.block><content.metadata.block><cmd.royalty><cmd.copyright><bop/><bos/>Westlaw. © 2019 Thomson Reuters.  <eos/><bos/>No Claim to Orig. U.S. Govt. <eos/><bos/>Works.<eos/><eop/></cmd.copyright></cmd.royalty><cmd.identifiers><cmd.cites><cmd.first.line.cite><bop/><bos/>GAEVIDENCE § 4:3<eos/><eop/></cmd.first.line.cite></cmd.cites></cmd.identifiers></content.metadata.block></doc></n-docbody>
